<!--
  House of Alden — sitemap.

  The pages that live at a fixed address and read the same for everybody:
  the six standing pages, plus one entry per journal post. Three of the site's
  HTML files are deliberately left out:

    cart.html    — per-visitor state, held in localStorage. It is a different
                   page for every reader and an empty one for a crawler, so
                   there is nothing here to index.

    product.html — a shell that reads ?id= from the address bar. Asked for on
                   its own it shows the "Not in the catalogue" notice, so the
                   bare address is not a page worth handing to a search engine.
                   NOTE: the eight product.html?id=… addresses this shell serves
                   ARE real pages, and each one carries its own Product/Offer
                   JSON-LD built by js/product.js. They are not listed here
                   because that list would have to be hand-copied from
                   js/config.js and would rot the first time stock changed —
                   config.js is meant to be the only place stock is edited.
                   They are reachable from collection.html, which is listed.

    404.html     — the dead end itself. It carries <meta name="robots"
                   content="noindex">, so listing it would ask a crawler to
                   fetch a page it is told not to keep.

  When a journal post is added to js/config.js and its page is written, add a
  <url> for it below. This file does not read config.js — it is the one place
  a new post has to be repeated by hand.

  The addresses are absolute, which is what the sitemap format requires — so
  this file is one of the places ./set-domain.sh rewrites when the domain
  changes. Update <lastmod> when a page's content actually changes; it is a
  claim about the page, not about the sitemap.
-->
